{
  "text": "These compounds undergo various processes in the environment, both in the non-living part of the environment and in organisms that were exposed to them in their habitat. The environmental fate of endocrine disruptors is shown schematically in Fig. 4 [CITATION_1] . Compounds included in this group, just like other types of xenobiotics, may undergo the bioaccumulation process in tissues and organs of organisms at higher trophic levels. This thesis is confirmed by data on toxaphene presented in Table 3 .",
